This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on interpreting machine learning systems, specifically tree ensembles. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning techniques, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the mention of medical and retail banking/finance applications suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), respectively. Finally, the use of similarity metrics and wandering among transparent trees suggests a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
